 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Agnes Friskeny was born in 1268, in Frampton, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom, her father, Ralph Friskeny, was 29 and her mother, Mrs RALPH FRISKENY, was 29. She married Roger Copledike. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"12680000–":"1268–Surnud","1268–Female":"1268–Surnud","1266–1324":"1266–1324","1290–1334":"1290–1334","1240–Male":"1240–Surnud","1240–Female":"1240–Surnud","12680000":"1268","Abt 1260":"umbes 1260","1324":"1324","1334":"1334","1268":"1268","1266":"1266","1240":"1240","Abt 1290":"umbes 1290","1290":"1290","of Frampton, Lincolnshire, England":"Frampton, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Of, Frampton, Lincolnshire, England":"Frampton, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom",",,England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"12680000–":"1268–Kuollut","1268–Female":"1268–Kuollut","1266–1324":"1266–1324","1290–1334":"1290–1334","1240–Male":"1240–Kuollut","1240–Female":"1240–Kuollut","12680000":"1268","Abt 1260":"noin 1260","1324":"1324","1334":"1334","1268":"1268","1266":"1266","1240":"1240","Abt 1290":"noin 1290","1290":"1290","of Frampton, Lincolnshire, England":"Frampton, Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Of, Frampton, Lincolnshire, England":"Frampton, Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta",",,England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"12680000–":"1268–Décédée","1268–Female":"1268–Décédée","1266–1324":"1266–1324","1290–1334":"1290–1334","1240–Male":"1240–Décédé","1240–Female":"1240–Décédée",